longBusinessSummary: Gold Port Corporation, exploration stage junior mining company, identifies, acquires, and explores for mineral properties in Canada and Guyana. The company holds a 100% interest in the Groete gold copper project covering an area of approximately 3,000 hectares located in Guyana. It also has an option to acquire 100% interest in the L.A.B. Graphite project situated in Quebec, Canada. The company was formerly known as Corsurex Resource Corp. and changed its name to Gold Port Corporation in September 2020. Gold Port Corporation was incorporated in 2016 and is headquartered in Vancouver, Canada.
